Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Trim the @carrot{2}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}, then cut each half into 3-4 wedges.

Pop the veg onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{150%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @chives{1%bunch} (use #scissors{} if easier).

When the veg has 8-10 mins of roasting time left, add the green beans to the same tray.

Toss to coat in the oil and seasoning. Return the tray to the oven for the remaining time.

== Creamy Pesto Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a #medium saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, fry the garlic for ~{1%min}.

Add the @creme fraiche{75%grams}, @fresh pesto{50%grams}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce. Stir well to combine, then simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{2-3%mins}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, share the roasted veg between your plates.

Drizzle over the pesto cream sauce, then sprinkle over the @toasted flaked almonds{15%grams} and chives to finish.

Enjoy!